# Content Strategy & ZAG Matrix Integration

## Content Creation Principles
- Every piece of content must serve "Alex, the Awakened Technologist"
- Connect all insights back to ZEN, ACT, GEM framework
- Use specific examples from Sheridan's executive career
- Maintain professional authority while being approachable
- Focus on actionable, implementable advice

## Content structure (blog)
- **Source of truth:** Markdown/MDX files in **`content/blog/`** at repo root (see [website/lib/posts.ts](mdc:website/lib/posts.ts))
- **Categories (frontmatter):** ZEN, ACT, GEM, ZAG, Featured — align folders under `content/blog/` with pillars where applicable
- **Detail:** [website/BLOG_SYSTEM_README.md](mdc:website/BLOG_SYSTEM_README.md) for frontmatter, slugs, authors, images
- Do not describe Contentlayer or `website/posts/` as the blog pipeline

## Blog content strategy
- **ZEN:** Clarity, purpose, mental resilience
- **ACT:** Physical well-being, relationships, momentum
- **GEM:** Strategic growth, entrepreneurship, career advancement
- Mix framework explanations with practical application and personal stories

## Newsletter
- The ZAG Navigator (Beehiiv); ZAG Matrix integration throughout
- Actionable strategies; community prompts where appropriate

## SEO & distribution
- Primary site: sheridanrichey.com
- Internal linking to ZAG Matrix and pillar content
- Meta titles/descriptions consistent with frontmatter and page `generateMetadata` where implemented

## Metrics (orientation)
- Newsletter engagement; blog traffic and time on page; resource downloads; subscriber growth
